ce:section.ce:para:
PEF, SAR, LEV, and BA were purchased from Macleans (Shanghai, China). Deionized water (resistivity 18.2 MΩ/cm) was prepared using a Millipore water purification system (Burlington, MA, USA). Afterglow decay curves, fluorescence decay curves, and TRESs were obtained on an Edinburgh Fluorescence spectrometer (FLS920P, Livingston, UK) full-featured fluorescence spectroscopy system. Fluorescence spectra and afterglow spectra were obtained through a fluorescence spectrophotometer (F-320, GANGDONG, Tianjin, China). Two transmission electron microscopes (JEM-2100PLUS and JEM-1400Flash, Osaka, Japan) were used to investigate the morphology of CDs. The XRD spectra were obtained by a SmartLab X-ray powder diffractometer (Tochigi, Japan). The FT-IR spectra were measured using a Nicolet 6700 FT-IR spectrometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Waltham, MA, USA). XPS data were collected on a Thermo ESCALAB 250 X-ray photoelectron spectrometer (Thermo Scientific). UV-vis absorption spectra were carried out by UV-vis diffuse reflectance spectrometer (Cary 7000, Agilent, Santa Clara, CA, USA). The UV lamp used in the experiment is a portable UV analyzer (ZF-5, 365 nm) produced by JiaPeng Technology. The fluorescent lamp used in the experiment is the NEXTORCH P80 flashlight. The absolute PLQYs (φ

                           PLQYs
                        ) of all solid-state compounds were measured using an absolute photoluminescence (PL) quantum yield spectrometer (Quantaurus-QY Plus/FLS1000) equipped with an integrating sphere under ambient conditions.
